1
00:00:14,933 --> 00:00:16,400
Please, don't hurt me.

2
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:18,433
Amanda, it's me, Lucho.

3
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:20,100
Look at me.

4
00:00:20,967 --> 00:00:22,000
I'm your friend.

5
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:23,700
Lucho?

6
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:29,433
I want to give you
a lavish wedding.

7
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:30,900
Thank you, Auntie.

8
00:00:30,967 --> 00:00:32,333
Red will be happy to hear that.

9
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:35,367
I hope we don't
rush your wedding.

10
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:38,567
Because you are
pregnant already.

11
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:42,067
And soon, it will be noticeable.

12
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:45,300
I don't want people
to talk against you.

13
00:00:45,367 --> 00:00:46,100
You know what I mean.

14
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,133
Are you agreeing with my mom?

15
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:51,767
She's just protecting us
against judgmental people.

16
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:53,367
Are you sure that's
the only reason?

17
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:56,567
I don't want you to
fight with your mom.

18
00:00:56,633 --> 00:00:59,033
I don't want to cause
your family any trouble.

19
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,033
She has good reason.

20
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:03,600
And it's for our own good.

21
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,300
Don't cry.

22
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:07,333
They can't hurt you anymore.

23
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,100
I'm here now.

24
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:10,767
I will never leave you.

25
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:11,867
I will help you.

26
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:15,600
Since the baby and I are
stable now,

27
00:01:15,667 --> 00:01:17,900
can we go look  for my mom?

28
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:21,233
I will feel guilty if something
bad happens to her.

29
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:22,267
I can't bear it.

30
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:25,800
So, Red, please
let's find my mom.

31
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:29,300
What they did to you is awful.

32
00:01:30,933 --> 00:01:32,633
You went to jail for
something you didn't do.

33
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:36,800
But destiny put my patience
to the test.

34
00:01:37,367 --> 00:01:40,667
Their son got Eden pregnant.

35
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:43,100
And now I'm all alone.

36
00:01:43,167 --> 00:01:44,733
You'll never be alone, Amanda.

37
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:50,200
I will do everything you want
to make you feel better.

38
00:01:50,267 --> 00:01:51,700
What if I want to get revenge?

39
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:53,900
I will help you.

40
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:13,800
Come on, Eden.

41
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:18,400
Why are you still
looking for your mom?

42
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:26,333
If she wants to be in your life,
she will come here.

43
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:29,133
But she didn't do that.

44
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:33,733
She doesn't care, Eden.

45
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,833
Something bad could
have happened to her.

46
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,467
That's why she
couldn't visit me.

47
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:43,067
Really?

48
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:47,833
Just admit that she's
so mad at you.

49
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:49,800
That's why she doesn't
show up here.

50
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:54,400
Eden, you have to
accept the truth.

51
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,700
Your mom doesn't
love you anymore.

52
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:06,067
She disowned you because she
couldn't accept what happened.

53
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:10,867
For short, she cut you off.

54
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:13,600
She considers you dead.

55
00:03:15,133 --> 00:03:16,667
That's why we're here.

56
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:22,800
I hope you guys can
appreciate that.

57
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,567
Mom, we appreciate you.

58
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:31,867
You too, Red!

59
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:35,300
You're in this, too,

60
00:03:35,367 --> 00:03:37,833
instead of teaching her
to do the right thing.

61
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:42,767
I did everything
for both of you.

62
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:47,667
I accepted you wholeheartedly.

63
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:49,733
I didn't reprove you.

64
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:52,633
You didn't hear anything
from me, right?

65
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:55,500
I'm always here for you.

66
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:57,200
I'm always by your side.

67
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:03,967
Only to find out you're looking
for this person...

68
00:04:04,433 --> 00:04:07,533
who hates you and doesn't
care about you.

69
00:04:08,567 --> 00:04:11,800
And you even hid it from me.

70
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:14,133
It's so unfair.

71
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,867
It hurts.

72
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:19,233
Am I not giving you enough love?

73
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,967
Not enough care?

74
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,633
Concern that I'm giving you?

75
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:28,900
Is that not enough?

76
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:32,667
Mom...

77
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:34,467
I'm sorry.

78
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,833
We didn't try to
hide it from you.

79
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,533
We just didn't tell you sooner.

80
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,033
I'm sorry.

81
00:04:44,767 --> 00:04:49,467
Auntie, we appreciate your help.

82
00:04:49,533 --> 00:04:54,200
I appreciate what you did
for me, Red, and our baby.

83
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:56,033
Thank you.

84
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:59,267
Sorry, we won't do it again.

85
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:02,100
I'll just wait for my mom
to come and visit me.

86
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:04,167
I'm sorry, Auntie.

87
00:05:20,133 --> 00:05:21,433
Yen...

88
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,133
aren't you tired?

89
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,400
You've been watering the plants
for a while now.

90
00:05:25,067 --> 00:05:25,767
What are you talking about?

91
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,467
I need to move around.

92
00:05:27,933 --> 00:05:30,067
Because I'm due to give birth.

93
00:05:31,767 --> 00:05:35,067
And I don't want it
to go to waste.

94
00:05:35,167 --> 00:05:36,867
I planted this myself.

95
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:38,467
It might die if
I don't water it.

96
00:05:39,767 --> 00:05:43,367
I want to see the flowers
before I give birth.

97
00:05:45,367 --> 00:05:47,867
Sir, there's a delivery
for Ma'am Eden.

98
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,600
Eden Sta. Maria?

99
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:51,833
Yeah, she's here.

100
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:54,767
I didn't order anything.

101
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:57,300
It's addressed here.

102
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,367
It might be wrong.

103
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,100
I'll go get it.

104
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,533
Did you order some food?

105
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:09,767
No.

106
00:06:12,267 --> 00:06:13,133
I wonder what it is.

107
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:22,533
No one died here.

108
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,333
Sir, please receive this.

109
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,667
No.

110
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,600
We're not taking that!

111
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:45,567
Send that back to the owner!

112
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:48,667
I'm not going to take that!

113
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:50,533
Send that back to Miss Amanda!

114
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:54,867
Red, he's just doing his job.

115
00:06:55,567 --> 00:06:56,933
You can go now, Sir.

116
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,567
- Go on!
- What's going on here ?

117
00:06:58,633 --> 00:07:00,033
- Get out of here!
- Red.

118
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:01,333
Who are you screaming at?

119
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,400
Funeral flower wreath?

120
00:07:08,367 --> 00:07:09,733
Is it for Eden?

121
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,267
From Amanda?

122
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:17,067
Okay, thank you.

123
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:25,733
What the heck is this?

124
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:29,833
They said they didn't know
the address of the sender.

125
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,167
But it comes
with a necklace!

126
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:33,200
It's so obvious that
Amanda sent that!

127
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,867
She's so evil!

128
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:38,800
When is she going to
leave us in peace?

129
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,933
And you, Eden!

130
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:43,100
You're even looking for her!

131
00:07:43,167 --> 00:07:44,500
Look at what she did.

132
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:45,967
Now you know that she's alive.

133
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:47,933
But you're dead to her.

134
00:07:48,033 --> 00:07:49,367
How could she send you
that flower wreath?

135
00:07:49,933 --> 00:07:50,900
The nerve!

136
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:55,700
Perhaps you'll believe me now.

137
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:58,033
That your mom is worthless.

138
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:03,400
Can you imagine she's
treating you dead?

139
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,500
She's still mad at me.

140
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:11,933
Doesn't she know that
she's hurting you?

141
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:13,800
I'm sorry, Yen.

142
00:08:13,867 --> 00:08:15,833
But I'm starting to hate her.

143
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:19,000
I can't blame you, Red.
I'm upset too.

144
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:23,233
I just don't get why
she hates me so much.

145
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:27,200
If I were you, Eden,

146
00:08:27,267 --> 00:08:30,500
I would give her a dose
of her own medicine.

147
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:37,233
If she treats you dead,
then do the same.

148
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:40,000
Just imagine she's dead too.

149
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:47,667
I understand how unfortunate
you are to have her as a mom.

150
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:55,967
But you're still lucky because
you met Red and our family.

151
00:08:56,800 --> 00:09:00,000
We treat you as our own, right?

152
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:02,900
So, don't be sad.

153
00:09:03,467 --> 00:09:08,400
Just think about the baby, okay?

154
00:09:32,933 --> 00:09:34,100
Eden.

155
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:36,467
Amanda...

156
00:09:37,433 --> 00:09:38,167
what's wrong?

157
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,933
I'm just thinking
about my daughter.

158
00:09:53,633 --> 00:09:55,867
I know that they
brainwashed her.

159
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,800
That was Rina's plan all along.

160
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:05,033
She wanted to take my daughter
away from me to get her revenge.

161
00:10:07,033 --> 00:10:08,600
Well, I'll beat her to it.

162
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:13,800
As I said, I will help you.

163
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:21,167
I will do whatever you want.

164
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,200
Thank you, Lucho.

165
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:28,500
I won't say no to that.

166
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:32,200
I will take revenge on Rina.

167
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:35,067
And I'm about to start.

168
00:10:37,167 --> 00:10:38,833
I don't understand Eden.

169
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:42,200
She's letting her crazy
mother get to her.

170
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,133
Keep it down.

171
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,333
She might hear you.

172
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:47,700
Why? I'm just telling the truth.

173
00:10:49,133 --> 00:10:52,667
And if Eden is in
her right mind,

174
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:57,500
she should hate her mother after
everything she's done.

175
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:01,233
You have to understand her too.
Eden is a good girl.

176
00:11:01,633 --> 00:11:04,233
She can't turn her back on
her mom just like that.

177
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:06,800
Or maybe she's crazy
like her mom.

178
00:11:10,867 --> 00:11:12,033
Who's calling me?

179
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,300
Hello?

180
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,567
Hello?

181
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:20,767
I will kill you.

182
00:11:21,367 --> 00:11:23,067
I will kill all of you.

183
00:11:23,467 --> 00:11:24,233
Who is this?

184
00:11:25,467 --> 00:11:27,533
I will kill you first.
You beast!

185
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:30,100
The nerve of you!
Who are you?

186
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:30,967
Who's this?

187
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:32,433
I will kill all of you!

188
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,000
I will kill you!

189
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:34,533
No!
No!

190
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:36,633
Stop this! No!

191
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,067
Rina, Rina!

192
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:39,467
- What's wrong?
- My God!

193
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:49,033
Are you okay now, Hon?

194
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:52,100
Do you think I'm okay?

195
00:11:52,167 --> 00:11:52,900
Are you serious?

196
00:11:52,967 --> 00:11:56,333
I still hear the
caller's voice.

197
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,067
It feels like she's near us.

198
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:01,867
She said she'll kill us all.

199
00:12:01,933 --> 00:12:03,767
She'll kill me first.

200
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:05,100
Victor, I'm scared!

201
00:12:05,167 --> 00:12:07,200
I'm scared for all of us!

202
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:09,133
Mom, don't you think
it's just a prank call?

203
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,700
Maybe you're just
letting it get to you.

204
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:12,333
What do you mean by prank call?

205
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,133
Come on!

206
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,200
That was a death threat!

207
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,367
Letting myself get affected?

208
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:18,167
I cannot take that lightly!

209
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:22,167
The other day we received
a funeral flower wreath.

210
00:12:22,233 --> 00:12:22,800
And now, a death threat.

211
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,533
I think this is serious.

212
00:12:26,233 --> 00:12:29,967
And I am so sure that only one
person can do this to us.

213
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:31,700
It's Amanda.

214
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:32,933
This is Amanda's doing.

215
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,767
She's the only person
who hates us this much.

216
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:38,033
There's a chance that it
wasn't my mom, Auntie.

217
00:12:39,233 --> 00:12:41,567
Not your mom? Who else
would do this?

218
00:12:41,633 --> 00:12:45,633
She sent you, her daughter,
a funeral flower.

219
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,167
What more if it's me?

220
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:49,667
She blames me for getting
separated from you.

221
00:12:50,633 --> 00:12:53,467
Is there anyone else
I can suspect?

222
00:12:53,533 --> 00:12:54,200
Tell me!

223
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,400
I know the people
who abused you.

224
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:07,533
I know Rina Ramos and
her brother Zandro.

225
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:09,133
You know them?

226
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:15,633
I couldn't believe it when
I heard your story.

227
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,633
Those people who
messed with you,

228
00:13:19,067 --> 00:13:22,433
Rina Ramos and Zandro,

229
00:13:23,233 --> 00:13:24,933
I've known them for a long time.

230
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:29,700
I've been watching them.

231
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:35,900
Did you know that they
have an illegal business?

232
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:37,733
Wait.

233
00:13:38,367 --> 00:13:42,133
Victor, Rina's husband,
works at the bank.

234
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:47,733
Victor has no idea about
his wife's shenanigans.

235
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,800
Rina is involved in a
large-scale loan business.

236
00:13:51,067 --> 00:13:54,067
They lend money to people
with gambling addiction.

237
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:59,967
When someone can't pay,
Zandro does the dirty work.

238
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:08,333
They've been torturing people,
just like what they did to you.

239
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:17,100
Here.

240
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,667
Choose one for you.

241
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,400
Lucho.

242
00:14:24,967 --> 00:14:25,667
Why...

243
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:27,000
why do you have these things?

244
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:29,467
It's just some of my collection.

245
00:14:29,967 --> 00:14:31,000
Don't be scared.

246
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,900
You want to take revenge,

247
00:14:41,967 --> 00:14:43,367
- don't you?
- I do.

248
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,633
But...

249
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:50,167
You should have the courage when
you make the decision.

250
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,200
They're monsters.

251
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:17,233
They have money and weapons,
just like me.

252
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:23,067
So, Amanda, you need
to prepare for them.

253
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:25,733
How about you?

254
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:27,933
Why are you wealthy?

255
00:15:28,533 --> 00:15:30,133
Why are you armed?

256
00:15:33,467 --> 00:15:36,667
Rina and I are living
in the same world.

257
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:39,067
But they don't know me.

258
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:44,867
At first, I thought my business
rival was Mr. Akashi.

259
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:49,767
I found out he was
just a financier.

260
00:15:50,767 --> 00:15:53,200
Rina and Zandro are his people.

261
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:58,467
Rina and Zandro are the
threats to my business.

262
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:04,333
So you're helping me because
you want to bring them down?

263
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:10,267
And because I still love you.

264
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,400
Now it's your choice...

265
00:16:16,867 --> 00:16:20,567
if you want to take revenge
against the Ramoses.

266
00:16:21,633 --> 00:16:23,167
But if you're weak...

267
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:28,767
maybe this isn't for you.

268
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:15,833
Auntie?

269
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:20,233
Sorry for everything
my mom is doing.

270
00:17:21,167 --> 00:17:22,933
I know what she does is wrong.

271
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,833
I apologize on her behalf.

272
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:33,067
I already expected that
from Amanda, Eden.

273
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:37,933
Your mom does that
because she's evil.

274
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:46,167
I hope you and your child
don't take after her.

275
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:51,600
If only I could
talk to her.

276
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:53,433
I would tell her to stop.

277
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:02,667
She's at it again.

278
00:18:02,733 --> 00:18:03,933
Someone's calling me again.

279
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,733
- I don't know who this is.
- Let me answer it, Auntie.

280
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:06,900
- It might be...
- That's her!

281
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:08,733
Let me take the call.

282
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:09,567
Gosh!

283
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,233
Hello?

284
00:18:15,533 --> 00:18:17,067
Hello, Mom?

285
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:18,467
Mom, is that you?

286
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:20,333
Mom, this is Eden.

287
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:22,500
Mom, please answer me.

288
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:23,100
That's enough.

289
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,300
Mom!

290
00:18:24,667 --> 00:18:26,100
Mom, if this is you,
please stop!

291
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:27,167
It's embarrassing!

292
00:18:27,233 --> 00:18:27,800
Give it to me.
- That's enough.
- Mom!

293
00:18:28,367 --> 00:18:29,100
That's enough.
- What's going on?
- Enough.

294
00:18:30,767 --> 00:18:32,333
It won't do your baby any good.

295
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:32,867
See?

296
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:34,900
She called again.

297
00:18:34,967 --> 00:18:38,933
Eden thought it was her
mom on the other line.

298
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,367
She wanted to talk to her.

299
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:45,567
Yen, you shouldn't
have done that.

300
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:47,467
You should have just ignored it.

301
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,733
Mom, you should have
just blocked the number.

302
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,833
Yeah, but she can always
buy a new sim, right?

303
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,000
And then it's a new number.

304
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,567
If you don't know the number,
then don't answer it.

305
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:00,367
Auntie, I'm sorry.

306
00:19:01,233 --> 00:19:03,900
I'm so ashamed of
what's happening.

307
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,967
Amanda is so evil.

308
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:11,100
I'm sorry, but I
have to say this.

309
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:13,300
She's mental.

310
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:17,367
She's not in her right mind.

311
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:21,867
I hope...

312
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:30,467
I hope one day she'll stop
and give our family some peace.

313
00:19:53,867 --> 00:19:55,200
You'll pay for it, Rina.

314
00:19:55,267 --> 00:19:57,000
I won't let you have peace.

315
00:19:58,267 --> 00:20:00,133
You will pay for what
you owe me.

316
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,333
You and your evil brother.

317
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,933
I will take my daughter back.
Brace yourself.

318
00:20:18,233 --> 00:20:19,700
Eden.

319
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,633
Amanda,

320
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:37,400
I don't think this is the right
time to meet your daughter.

321
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:43,700
You're right.

322
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:47,633
I'll come back when I'm ready.

323
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:50,600
Let's go.

324
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:22,200
Hello, Zandro.

325
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:23,333
Yes, Rina.

326
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:24,533
How is it going?

327
00:21:25,933 --> 00:21:28,833
You're so good at messing up
with people.

328
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:32,633
They're so convinced that
Amanda was sending those

329
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:34,533
death threats.

330
00:21:56,333 --> 00:21:58,200
I'm ready for you, Rina.

331
00:22:02,667 --> 00:22:07,900
I will toy with you first
before I bring you down.

332
00:22:07,967 --> 00:22:13,200
You will suffer the
way you made me suffer.

333
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:17,400
You will feel every
inch of my wrath.

334
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:37,900
Forgive me, Eden,
for what I'm about to do.

335
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:40,533
But everything I will do
is for you.

336
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:45,300
To take you away
from the people you trust.

337
00:22:45,367 --> 00:22:47,433
I hope it's not too late.

338
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:49,100
Gave birth?

339
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:49,933
How did it happen?

340
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,300
It's not her due yet.

341
00:22:51,367 --> 00:22:53,000
She's only in her 8th month.

342
00:22:55,667 --> 00:22:59,000
I showed you my world
so you'd get to know me.

343
00:22:59,067 --> 00:23:02,267
And for you to be aware of the
world you got yourself into.

344
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:05,033
I don't care about your
illegal activities.

345
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:07,967
I just want to get revenge
and take my daughter back.

346
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:11,600
You're no longer
the Amanda they know.

347
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:14,400
You're now Mrs. Madrigal.
